<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I Don't Get It... (txt)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Parasite Eve">Parasite Eve</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:54 p.m. 25/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I Don't Get It... (txt)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>You have a choice as to whether or not to play on the PvP shard. On the other shards, you can challenge people to duels, so you can still engage in PvP there, get that "enrichment" of your role-playing environment, & not have to worry about being "mindlessly PK'd".

<P>I honestly can't believe that ANYONE who CHOOSES to play on Rallos Zek would ever think of complaining about getting "mindlessly" PK'd.
<P>I really can't. I'm even talking about corpse campers, rez killers, & newbie killers, & same-race killers.
<P>Jeez, people, you can't POSSIBLY tell me you weren't prepared for it -- especially those of you who ever played UO, you people IN PARTICULAR need to be ashamed of yourself if you ever whine about getting PK'd on Rallos Zek. You UO veterans damn sure knew about jerks & cretins & power-gamers & such, & you knew damn well they'd be playing EQ, & you knew damn well they'd be flocking to the PvP shard... so, you've only yourselves to blame.
<P>Got PK'd? Get better, get stronger, & DEAL WITH IT. But seriously, this board is for talking about getting better at it, so you won't die so easily next time. If you quit whining, & maybe listen more, you'll learn something.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
